  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>wedges</strong> to a large baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up </p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until the wedges are tender and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the wedges are cooking, drain and rinse the <strong>chickpeas</strong> and add them to a <strong>food processor</strong></p>\n<p>Juice the <strong>lemon</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> into the processor</p>\n<p>Peel the <strong>garlic </strong>and chop roughly<strong> </strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>tahini</strong>, 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, a splash of <strong>water</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>salt</strong> to the processor</p>\n<p>Blitz until smooth and creamy then set aside – this is your <strong>hummus </strong></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>diced chicken</strong> to a mixing bowl with the <strong>ras el hanout</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and most of the<strong> smoked paprika</strong> (save a pinch for garnish!)</p>\n<p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mix to combine the chicken in the spices</p>\n<p>Peel and finely slice the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/801.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
